<body>

<h1>CHAPTER 4: SYSTEM IMPLEMENTATION AND TESTING</h1>

<h2>4.1 Technologies and Tools Used</h2>
<p>The KaviCakes Management System is a complete software solution built with three main parts: the Admin Web Dashboard, the Customer Web Portal, and a central API Backend. Both web platforms talk to the same backend server. This ensures that all business rules, prices, and security checks are controlled in one safe place.</p>
<p>The system stores image files, such as payment bank slips, in a local folder on the server. Older product images are safely stored in a cloud service called Supabase. The system connects to a MySQL database to securely save all customer accounts, orders, and financial records.</p>

<h2>4.2 Programming Languages and Development Tools</h2>

<h3>4.2.1 Backend — Node.js and Express.js</h3>
<p>The API is built using Node.js and the Express.js framework. This setup was chosen because it can process many customer orders at the same time without slowing down. The database is managed using Prisma ORM, a tool that links the database to the code and prevents saving wrong data types. Passwords are secured using a strong encryption tool called Bcryptjs and are never saved as normal text. The system also uses JWT to keep users securely logged in.</p>
<p>Emails are sent using the Nodemailer tool, and automated daily tasks (like sending delivery reminders) are handled using a tool called node-cron.</p>

<h3>4.2.2 Admin Web — React and Vite</h3>
<p>The Admin Dashboard is built with React and bundled using Vite for faster performance. The design uses Ant Design, which provides readymade, professional tables, forms, and buttons perfect for admin tasks. The dashboard correctly tracks live data, like changing order numbers and daily income. It also checks if the admin is logged in securely; if not, it sends them back to the login page immediately.</p>

<h3>4.2.3 Customer Web — React and Tailwind CSS</h3>
<p>The Customer Web Portal is also built using React, but its design is styled using Tailwind CSS. This allows the customer site to have a unique, colorful, and mobile-friendly look. The system uses React state management to instantly update the screen. For example, when a customer changes a cake size, the price on the screen updates immediately without reloading the page.</p>

<h2>4.3 User Interface Demonstration and Data Entry Screens</h2>
<p>The system's screens are separated based on who is logging in. An Admin sees the order lists, cashbook, and inventory. A Customer only sees the cake catalog, their personal profile, and their own order history.</p>

<h3>4.3.1 Authentication</h3>
<p>When a new customer registers, they must enter a 6-digit OTP sent to their email to prove their identity before logging in. Forms will show red error warnings if passwords are too weak or phone numbers are typed incorrectly. Standard customers cannot access the admin login page.</p>
