<h3>4.3.4 Product Customization (Variants)</h3>
<p>Instead of a simple "Add" button, the cake details page has drop-down lists. Customers must select a size, flavor, and shape. As they change these options, the system immediately calculates and displays the new total cost before the item enters the cart.</p>
<span class="image-message">[Insert Image: Single Product View with Variant Calculators]</span>

<h3>4.3.5 Cart, Checkout, and Payment</h3>
<p>During checkout, the screens change based on what the user selects. If they select "Online Payment", they must pay the full amount. If they select "Cash on Delivery", the screen displays a warning that a 30% advance deposit must be uploaded. Customers can also slide a bar to use their Loyalty Points to reduce the final bill.</p>
