<h3>4.3.9 Notification Hub</h3>
<p>This page allows the admin to edit the text for the automated email messages. They can also manually send an email to all customers at once if there is a special promotion or holiday.</p>
<span class="image-message">[Insert Image: Notice Control Hub]</span>

<h2>4.4 Quality Assurance Methods Used</h2>
<p>Testing was done carefully throughout development. First, all forms were tested by typing incorrect details (like letters in a phone number box) to make sure the system blocked them and showed error messages. Security testing was done by trying to visit admin pages using a standard customer account, which the system successfully blocked.</p>
<p>Finally, manual end-to-end testing was performed. We created a test customer account, added cakes to the cart, selected a delivery address, uploaded a test bank slip, and completed the order. Then, we logged in as the Admin, verified the slip, and moved the order step-by-step from 'New' to 'Delivered' to confirm the entire process works perfectly without any errors.</p>

<h2>4.5 Key Libraries and Justification</h2>
<p>Specific libraries were chosen to solve certain problems easily:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Prisma:</strong> Used instead of writing raw SQL code. It prevents database crashing errors by checking data types before saving.</li>
    <li><strong>Bcryptjs:</strong> Used to strongly encrypt user passwords so they are safe even if the database is accessed by hackers.</li>
    <li><strong>Nodemailer:</strong> Used because it connects securely to external email services, ensuring customers receive their OTPs quickly.</li>
    <li><strong>Ant Design:</strong> Chosen for the admin side because it provides ready-to-use professional tables and forms, saving development time.</li>
    <li><strong>Tailwind CSS:</strong> Used on the customer side to style the web pages quickly without writing long, messy CSS files.</li>
    <li><strong>Axios:</strong> Used to connect the frontend to the backend because it easily attaches the secure JWT login token to every request automatically.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4.6 Core Business Logic and System Automations</h2>
<p>The following logic rules handle the unique business operations of KaviCakes securely in the backend code.</p>

<h3>4.6.1 Authentication & Security</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Multi-Role System:</strong> The system strictly supports ADMIN and CUSTOMER roles, keeping their access completely separate.</li>
    <li><strong>Verified Registration:</strong> Users must verify their email via a 6-digit OTP before they can log in and place orders.</li>
    <li><strong>JWT Protection:</strong> Secured routes require a valid token in the Authorization header, preventing unauthorized access.</li>
    <li><strong>Admin Singleton:</strong> The system is configured to allow only one primary admin account for maximum security.</li>
</ul>

<h3>4.6.2 Product & Pricing Engine</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Variant Pricing:</strong> The system calculates the final price using this rule: <em>Final price = (Category Base Price * Size Multiplier) + Flavor Premium</em>.</li>
    <li><strong>Bulk Pricing:</strong> It implements a "Threshold" system. If a customer orders a quantity greater than the bulk limit, a lower bulk price is applied per unit automatically.</li>
    <li><strong>Availability Guard:</strong> The logic checks `isAvailable` flags on both the main cake product and the specific variants chosen before it allows the item into a shopping cart.</li>
</ul>

<h3>4.6.3 Order Lifecycle Logic</h3>
<p>This is the most complex part of the system, located securely in the `orderController.js` file.</p>
<table>
    <tr>
        <th>State</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Guardrails / Business Rules</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>NEW</strong></td>
        <td>Order created by customer.</td>
        <td>Loyalty Points are capped at 30% of the total. An urgency fee is automatically applied if delivery is needed in less than 48 hours.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>CONFIRMED</strong></td>
        <td>Admin acknowledged the order.</td>
        <td>Triggers an automated "Order Confirmed" email to the customer.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>PREPARING</strong></td>
        <td>Kitchen starts work.</td>
        <td><strong>Strict Guard:</strong> The Admin cannot start this stage unless the Advance (30%) or Full Payment is officially verified and approved.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>READY</strong></td>
        <td>Cake is boxed and ready.</td>
        <td>Triggers a notification for pickup or delivery.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>DELIVERED</strong></td>
        <td>Customer received order.</td>
        <td>Automatically generates a PDF Invoice and sends it to the customer's email.</td>
    </tr>
</table>

<h3>4.6.4 Payment & Advance Logic</h3>
<p>The system supports Cash on Delivery (30% Advance) and Full Online Payment.</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Bank Slip Verification:</strong> When a customer uploads a payment proof, the order enters a `PENDING_VERIFICATION` state so the admin can review the image manually.</li>
    <li><strong>Balance Tracking:</strong> The system calculates the total as `advanceAmount + balanceAmount`. The balance amount is updated dynamically if order items are edited later.</li>
    <li><strong>Manual Collection:</strong> Admins can record "In-Person Cash" payments in the dashboard, which then directly updates the daily cashbook.</li>
</ul>

<h3>4.6.5 Loyalty Point System</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Earning:</strong> Customers automatically earn 1 point for every Rs. 100 spent (calculated on the subtotal).</li>
    <li><strong>Spending:</strong> Customers can redeem existing points at checkout to receive an instant discount on their total bill.</li>
    <li><strong>Safety Rule:</strong> Point redemption is strictly capped at 30% of the gross total to maintain the bakery's profit margins.</li>
    <li><strong>Urgent Fee:</strong> Urgent orders with a short deadline automatically deduct an additional 500 points from the customer's balance as a priority processing fee.</li>
</ul>

